  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 190°C/ 170°C (fan)/ 375°F/ Gas 5</p><p>Remove the <strong>burrata</strong> from the fridge to bring to room temperature</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580131265900-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580131265900-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580131265900-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580131265900-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1580131265900-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until starting to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580131270004-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580131270004-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580131270004-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580131270004-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1580131270004-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to caramelise, slice the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced tomatoes</strong> to a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and gently stir together</p><p>Strip the<strong> thyme leaves</strong> from the stalks, discard the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580131273850-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580131273850-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580131273850-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580131273850-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1580131273850-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>puff pastry</strong> onto the lined baking tray</p><p>Score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife</p><p>Tip: The pastry border will puff up to give you a nice crust!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580131280238-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580131280238-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580131280238-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580131280238-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1580131280238-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>caramelised onions</strong> over the pastry within the border</p><p>Add the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> and top with the<strong> thyme leaves</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until the pastry is cooked through and puffed up – this is your <strong>confit tomato tart</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580131283887-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580131283887-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580131283887-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580131283887-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580131283887-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tart is cooking, boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork tender, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1580131287902-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1580131287902-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1580131287902-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1580131287902-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1580131287902-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>fig relish</strong> with the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>fig dressing</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the drained potatoes and season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1580131291389-x200.jpg",
